item.title: CVE-2021-26625|2024-08-03T20:26:25.640Z -- tobesoft%20co.%2Cltd -- nexacro%2017
item.description: Insufficient Verification of input Data leading to arbitrary file download and execute was discovered in Nexacro platform. This vulnerability is caused by an automatic update function that does not verify input data except version information. Remote attackers can use this incomplete validation logic to download and execute arbitrary malicious file.
